From Tony Lezard Subject Re atheist I Benedikt Rosenau writes In article Tony Lezard writes Deletion My opinion is that the strong atheist position requires too much belief for me to be comfortable Any strong atheists out there care to comment Humans just come up with the idea of a spiritual It is one of the artifacts of human The evidence for that is quite And the information content of the conceived is In other words if there were gods they would hardly make sense and it is possible to explain the phenomenon of religion without The concept is useless and I don't have to introduce new assumptions in order to show No leap of faith required for Your mileage may Yes I fully agree with that but is it I don't believe gods exist or I believe no gods exist As MANDTBACKA Mats Andtbacka pointed out it all hinges on what you take the word believe to Unfortunately this is bound up in the definitions of strong and weak atheism at least according to the FAQ Atheism is characterized by an absence of belief in the existence of Some atheists go further and believe that God does not The former is often referred to as the weak atheist position and the latter as strong atheism It is important to note the difference between these two Weak atheism is simple scepticism disbelief in the existence of Strong atheism is a positive belief that God does not Please do not fall into the trap of assuming that all atheists are strong atheists From mathew's An Introduction to Atheism version last modified Apr Should the FAQ be clarified to try to pin down this notion of belief Can it Tony Lezard IS OR tony OR things like tony relay OR last resort PGP public key available on